main event: Multiple objects traveling at high speeds were observed ascending vertically and disappearing into the clouds over Los Angeles, California on September 12, 1960.
interesting points: The objects were traveling at approximately 1,200 mph.
The witness reported seeing approximately 6 objects.
The objects appeared to be ascending vertically and then disappearing into the overcast sky.
No conclusions or evaluations were made in the original report.
The witness was unable to estimate the size or distance of the objects.
